## Devpost 300-Word Summary (Draft — complete after analysis)

Prediction markets like Polymarket and Kalshi let thousands of people bet real money on future events — Fed decisions, elections, Bitcoin prices. In theory they're the most accurate forecasting tools ever built. In practice, we wanted to know: where are they wrong, and where do they disagree with each other?

We built MarketPulse to answer that question automatically, in real time.

[INSERT KEY FINDING HERE ONCE CONFIRMED]

Our platform ingests live odds from both Polymarket and Kalshi, normalizes them into a unified format, and runs two analyses continuously. First, our arbitrage detector scans all active markets and flags cross-platform pricing discrepancies above a meaningful threshold. Second, our calibration engine measures whether each platform's prices are actually accurate — when a market is priced at 70%, does it resolve correctly 70% of the time?

Everything is served through three live REST API endpoints and an interactive dashboard. This isn't a notebook. It's a production system anyone can query right now.

